Apache 2.4 support (closes #3):
 - conn_rec->remote_ip / remote_addr were removed in Apache 2.4 in favour of
   the request-level useragent_ip / useragent_addr. The module now selects the
   right fields at compile time, so it builds and runs on both Apache 2.2
   (CentOS 6) and Apache 2.4 (CentOS 7). CI exercises both via a matrix.

Ported bug fixes from gnif/mod_rpaf:
 - Behind a chain of proxies, use the last forwarded entry that is not a
   trusted proxy as the client IP, instead of always taking the last entry.
 - Validate X-Forwarded-For entries and skip anything that does not look
   like an IP address (logged as a warning).
 - RPAFsetport sets the port per request via r->parsed_uri.port instead of
   mutating the shared server_rec, which previously leaked the port across
   requests and virtualhosts.

Additional fixes in the server_scheme / hostname / https handling:
 - RPAFsethttps no longer leaves r->server->server_scheme set to "https"
   after an https request; it is reset per request so plain-HTTP requests on
   the same server no longer generate https self-referential URLs.
 - RPAFsethttps validates the forwarded HTTPS header value (on/1/true/yes/
   https), so a value such as "off" is no longer treated as https.
 - RPAFsethostname uses the last entry of a comma-separated X-Forwarded-Host.

Keep Alive Problem reported and patched by Christian Schneider
 Also reported by Hiroyuki OYAMA and Vladimir Klebanov
mod_rpaf was incorrectly using r->pool to allocate memory for the
ip. The correct pool for this when you are dealing wth keep-alive
requests was r->connection->pool.

Adding configurable header to work with common Russian setups that
use X-Real-Ip instead of X-Forwarded-For.

Fixing problems with keep-alive connections reusing the original
X-Forwarded-For ip as the 'remote_ip'. 

Move the `change_remote_ip' handler from being APR_HOOK_MIDDLE to
APR_HOOK_FIRST to make the module run before modules like mod_geoip.

